''Shinobi''{{'}}s initial release fell on November 10, 2002 in North America; December 5 in Japan; and May 15, 2003 in Europe.<ref name="release">{{cite web|title=Related Games|url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/action/shinobi/similar.html?mode=versions|publisher=GameSpot|accessdate=April 28, 2010}}</ref>

In 2003, ''Shinobi'' was re-released in North America as part of [[Sony]]'s [[List of Sony Greatest Hits games|Greatest Hits]] budget line, signifying a sales total of at least 400,000 in that region. This edition includes a [[DVD]] containing a trailer for the upcoming Overworks game ''[[Kunoichi]]'' and gameplay footage played by experienced players.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kunoichi trailer to be included in Shinobi rerelease|date=June 23, 2003|last=Niizumi|first=Hirohiko|url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/action/shinobi/news.html?sid=6030468&mode=news|publisher=GameSpot|accessdate=April 25, 2010}}</ref> On September 25 of the same year, the game was re-released as part of Japan's similar [[The Best range|The Best]] budget line.<ref name="release"/>
